{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"frying pan, bowl, serving plates, baking paper, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), aluminium foil, whisk, oven, stove top","id":"r250023","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-6e9MIFsOhsM\/XZQICy7awkI\/AAAAAAAAcOw\/YeG5_a3Dwuowj8RJ1nE2NfcYTNmT_2dhQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_wJXTAQjsARFO-9Z5.png","title":"Lamb cutlets with spinach and pea purée","publishedAt":"2017-11-22T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"1 lamb rack, trimmed (see Tip)"},{"content":"¼ tsp salt, plus extra for seasoning"},{"content":"2 pinches ground black pepper, plus extra for seasoning"},{"content":"40 g olive oil, plus 1 tablespoon for frying"},{"content":"120 g red wine"},{"content":"1 tsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)"},{"content":"50 g Parmesan cheese, cut into pieces (3 cm)"},{"content":"10 g pickled capers, drained"},{"content":"2 garlic cloves"},{"content":"1 sprig fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only"},{"content":"1 sprig fresh mint, leaves only"},{"content":"1 sprig fresh basil, leaves only"},{"content":"500 g water, plus extra for cooking"},{"content":"450 g frozen peas"},{"content":"60 g fresh baby spinach leaves"},{"content":"1 lemon, zest only, no white pith"},{"content":"120 g pouring (whipping) cream"},{"content":"2 pinches ground nutmeg"},{"content":"1 tsp unsalted butter"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"35.8 g","fat":"40.5 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"11.1 g","calories":"2362 kJ \/ 562.5 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Season lamb with salt and pepper. Place a frying pan over high heat, add 1 tablespoon of the oil and sear lamb until browned. Transfer lamb onto prepared baking tray and set aside."},{"content":"Drain and discard any excess fat from the frying pan. Return frying pan to the heat and add wine. Cook wine for 2-3 minutes, until slightly reduced. Add stock paste and ½ cup water. Stir and simmer gently until reduced to a light jus (approx. 5 minutes). Set frying pan with jus aside."},{"content":"Place Parmesan into mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place remaining 40 g oil, capers, garlic, parsley, mint and basil into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of bowl with spatula and chop for a further <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Coat the top of the reserved lamb rack with herb paste. Place lamb into oven and roast for 15-20 minutes (200°C) or until cooked to your liking. Cover with aluminium foil and set aside to rest while making spinach and pea purée."},{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket, weigh peas into it and cook <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Place Varoma dish into position and weigh spinach into it. Secure Varoma lid and and cook <b>8 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b> or until peas are just cooked and spinach wilts. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula. Discard cooking liquid."},{"content":"Place peas, spinach, lemon zest, cream, nutmeg, reserved Parmesan and remaining salt and pepper into mixing bowl and blend <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and heat purée <b>2 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Place frying pan with reserved jus over medium-high heat. Add butter and whisk until melted and jus is smooth and glossy."},{"content":"Carve reserved lamb rack into individual cutlets. Divide purée between serving plates and top with lamb cutlets. Drizzle with reserved jus just before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Ask your butcher to trim your lamb rack for you - it's not hard to do yourself, but it can be time consuming.","To make your own Vegetable stock paste, please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i>."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}